{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_IWKxh3cHCpHsdtyGR9wE788x","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_specialist\n3\toutput:\n4\t  topic: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\t  errors: string\n7\tdependsOn: [inventory]\n8\tforEach: inventory.scopes\n9\trole: general\n10\tfunctions: []\n11\tcanDelegateTo:\n12\t  - system-architect/architect#synthesize_and_run\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tBuild ONE specialist from an inventoried scope. `item` is `{ topic, goal, research }`. The supplied\n16\tmaterial is the source, so do not research. Delegate to the architect with the item directly, then\n17\tpackage the result honestly. Emit these statements across turns:\n18\t\n19\tconst result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\n20\t\n21\tconst built = (result && result.data) ? result.data : { ok: false, errors: 'the architect returned no result' };\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({ topic: String(item.topic), ok: !!(result && result.ok === true && built.ok === true), errors: String(built.errors || '') });"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"4880fd5c-ff06-4c42-9289-9109f11426b9","timestamp":"2026-07-15T23:53:52.226Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/02-build_specialist.md","content":"---\nid: build_specialist\noutput:\n  topic: string\n  ok: boolean\n  errors: string\ndependsOn: [inventory]\nforEach: inventory.scopes\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\ncanDelegateTo:\n  - system-architect/architect#synthesize_and_run\n---\n\nBuild ONE specialist from an inventoried scope. `item` is `{ topic, goal, research }`. The supplied\nmaterial is the source, so do not research. Delegate to the architect with the item directly, then\npackage the result honestly. Emit these statements across turns:\n\nconst result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\n\nconst built = (result && result.data) ? result.data : { ok: false, errors: 'the architect returned no result' };\ncurrentTask.resolve({ topic: String(item.topic), ok: !!(result && result.ok === true && built.ok === true), errors: String(built.errors || '') });","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ivUkEJiAzrValJUNj7Cj6ues","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  request: string\n4\t  sourceSummary: string\n5\t  attachmentIds: array\n6\t  specialistFacts: string\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\tOrganize supplied material into a live-project app. First identify every independently owned scope\n10\tin the material; then build one grounded specialist for each scope in parallel; finally hand the\n11\tcomplete source to the automator. The goal output reports the specialist builds and app build."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"25acae19-505e-46c9-bc14-08750a0a5bb2","timestamp":"2026-07-15T23:53:52.227Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/index.md","content":"---\ninput:\n  request: string\n  sourceSummary: string\n  attachmentIds: array\n  specialistFacts: string\n---\n\nOrganize supplied material into a live-project app. First identify every independently owned scope\nin the material; then build one grounded specialist for each scope in parallel; finally hand the\ncomplete source to the automator. The goal output reports the specialist builds and app build.","numLines":11,"startLine":1,"totalLines":11}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_8G6o4wUeFxVbdFmrtVgt8UbU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: inventory\n3\toutput:\n4\t  scopes: array\n5\trole: explore\n6\tfunctions: []\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\tIdentify every independently owned scope in the supplied material. `request`, `sourceSummary`,\n10\t`attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every supplied document with\n11\t`readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope has its own facts and\n12\tdeserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because it has few facts. A\n13\tscope is a stable part of the user's material (such as a location, stage, person, client, or piece of\n14\tequipment), NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, or fact. Include every stable scope\n15\trepresented in the source, not only the most detailed ones.\n16\t\n17\tFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\n18\twith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\n19\tin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\n20\tis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:\n21\t\n22\tconst documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n23\t\n24\tcurrentTask.resolve({ scopes: [{ topic: \"<scope>\", goal: \"<what it should answer>\", research: { topic: \"<scope>\", executive_summary: \"<summary>\", findings: [{ heading: \"<facet>\", detail: \"<supplied facts>\" }], conclusion: \"\", sources: [] } }] });"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"8fbef77b-fbd5-4533-8373-04c17722e774","timestamp":"2026-07-15T23:53:52.228Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/01-inventory.md","content":"---\nid: inventory\noutput:\n  scopes: array\nrole: explore\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nIdentify every independently owned scope in the supplied material. `request`, `sourceSummary`,\n`attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every supplied document with\n`readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope has its own facts and\ndeserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because it has few facts. A\nscope is a stable part of the user's material (such as a location, stage, person, client, or piece of\nequipment), NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, or fact. Include every stable scope\nrepresented in the source, not only the most detailed ones.\n\nFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\nwith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\nin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\nis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:\n\nconst documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n\ncurrentTask.resolve({ scopes: [{ topic: \"<scope>\", goal: \"<what it should answer>\", research: { topic: \"<scope>\", executive_summary: \"<summary>\", findings: [{ heading: \"<facet>\", detail: \"<supplied facts>\" }], conclusion: \"\", sources: [] } }] });","numLines":24,"startLine":1,"totalLines":24}}}
