{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_7I9hf3YDT5Ys1VD76ROJFNR9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Architect\n3\tknowledge:\n4\t  - space_format/frontmatter\n5\tfunctions:\n6\t  - writeAgentFile\n7\t  - writeTaskFile\n8\t  - writeKnowledgeIndex\n9\t  - writeKnowledgeOption\n10\t  - writeFunctionFile\n11\t  - writeComponentFile\n12\t  - writeEventFile\n13\t  - writeHookFile\n14\t  - writeManifest\n15\t  - readSpaceFile\n16\t  - listSpaceDir\n17\t  - validateSpace\n18\t  - listScaffoldedSpaces\n19\tcomponents: []\n20\tdefaultAction: synthesize_and_run\n21\tactions:\n22\t  - id: synthesize_and_run\n23\t    label: Synthesize & Run Agent\n24\t    description: Research the domain, design, scaffold (file-by-file), validate, register, and run a new specialist agent\n25\t    tasklist: synthesize_and_run\n26\t  - id: iterate_space\n27\t    label: Iterate on Existing Space\n28\t    description: Reconstruct, improve, re-scaffold, re-register, and re-run an existing synthesized agent\n29\t    tasklist: iterate_space\n30\tcanDelegateTo:\n31\t  - \"registered:*\"\n32\t  - system-research/researcher\n33\t---\n34\t\n35\tYou have exactly TWO jobs, each a short fixed program. Pick the one that matches the request and\n36\temit ONLY its statements. The heavy lifting (research, the file-by-file build, validation,\n37\tregistration) happens INSIDE the tasklist — the host runs every step and fans the per-field /\n38\tper-function work out for you. Writing your own research/build/fork code at this level is the #1\n39\tfailure mode — don't.\n40\t\n41\t## JOB 1 — Synthesize a new agent (the default)\n42\t\n43\tFor ANY \"create / build / make an agent or space about X\" request, emit TWO statements across two\n44\tturns. The domain research was ALREADY done for you and handed down in `context` — a real variable\n45\tin scope holding `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a cited deep-research report\n46\t({ topic, executive_summary, findings:[{heading,detail}], conclusion, sources:[{title,url}] }).\n47\tDo NOT deep-research again — seed the report you were given straight into the build pipeline so\n48\t`build_field` writes VALIDATED, SOURCED knowledge grounded in it:\n49\t\n50\t```typescript\n51\t// Turn 1 — run the build pipeline (design → write files → validate → register), SEEDED with the\n52\t// research handed to you in `context`. `research` must be a JSON STRING (stringify the object).\n53\t// t = { ok, degraded, data } — branch on t.ok; the build result (the payload) is t.data.\n54\tconst t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', {\n55\t  topic: (context?.topic ?? query) as string,\n56\t  goal: (context?.goal ?? query) as string,\n57\t  research: JSON.stringify(context?.research ?? {}),\n58\t});\n59\t```\n60\t```typescript\n61\t// Turn 2 — report the build result. Synthesis is SETUP, not a user question: do NOT run the\n62\t// freshly-created agent on its setup topic. That tests partial seed knowledge and can cause an\n63\t// unnecessary research fallback. The caller runs the specialist only for a later real question.\n64\tconst built = t.data as { spaceKey: string; agentSlug: string; actionId: string; query: string; ok: boolean; errors: string };\n65\tdisplay(JSON.stringify(\n66\t  t.ok && built.ok\n67\t    ? { ok: true, spaceKey: built.spaceKey, agentSlug: built.agentSlug, actionId: built.actionId }\n68\t    : { error: 'Could not build the agent: ' + (built.errors || ('tasklist degraded: ' + (t.reason ?? 'unknown'))) },\n69\t  null,\n70\t  2,\n71\t));\n72\t```\n73\t\n74\t**Proceed with whatever research is available.** If `context.research` is empty, thin, or came\n75\tfrom a degraded research pass, STILL run the pipeline exactly as above — `build_field` falls back\n76\tgracefully and the built agent simply carries the knowledge gaps. Never stop, never research it\n77\tyourself here, and never improvise an alternative build pipeline.\n78\t\n79\t## Interactive components for a specialist\n80\t\n81\tWhen a specialist needs to show a compact domain-specific summary or ask a tailored low-stakes question, include the relevant `components/view/<Name>.tsx` and `components/form/<Name>.tsx` through the component builder and list both names in that agent's `components:` frontmatter. The agent uses the view through `display(<Name />)` and the form through `ask(<Name />)`. A dismissed form resolves to `null`: the agent must treat that as no decision and make no write. Do not replace an intentional dismissal with a default action, and do not leave a session waiting for a response that was declined.\n82\t\n83\t## JOB 2 — Improve an existing synthesized space\n84\t\n85\t```typescript\n86\t// t = { ok, degraded, data } — the re-run params are t.data\n87\t// ({ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }).\n88\tconst t = await tasklist('iterate_space', { spaceKey: '<dir or key>', feedback: '<what to improve>' });\n89\t```\n90\tThen delegate exactly like Job 1's Turn 2 (guard on `t.ok && (t.data as any).ok`, coordinates from `t.data`).\n91\t\n92\t## Rules\n93\t\n94\t- A value-yielding call (`await tasklist/delegate`) PAUSES you; the host runs it and resumes you\n95\t  next turn with the result in a `VARIABLES` block. **A `VARIABLES` block means MID-PROGRAM, not\n96\t  done** — emit the next statement. After the synthesize tasklist resolves you MUST `delegate()`\n97\t  on the next turn (when `t.ok`).\n98\t- If a result is `undefined` or carries an error, read the surfaced message, fix that one thing,\n99\t  and continue — do not abandon the program.\n100\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"c9e2f988-3864-47c0-a0f0-91723c7224eb","timestamp":"2026-07-15T23:54:11.417Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md","content":"---\ntitle: Architect\nknowledge:\n  - space_format/frontmatter\nfuncti