{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_UBUUaTml6A7CCJL0VkeVBTkb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# LMThing — Developer Onboarding\n2\t\n3\tWelcome to lmthing. This file is an **orientation index**: what the repo is, how to run it, and where to find the answer. It holds no knowledge of its own.\n4\t\n5\t## Read this first — `org/docs/` is the source of truth\n6\t\n7\t**[`org/docs/`](./org/docs/README.md) (published at lmthing.org) is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for this codebase.** Every factual sentence there is cited to the implementation with a symbol anchor (`path#Symbol`), falling back to a line anchor (`path:Lstart-Lend`) only where a symbol isn't appropriate. `pnpm docs:check` resolves every citation as a hard CI gate. When this file, a `.claude/skill`, or any README disagrees with `org/docs/`, **`org/docs/` wins**; when `org/docs/` disagrees with the **code**, the **code** wins and the doc is a bug.\n8\t\n9\t> **A code change is not done until the matching `org/docs/` page is updated in the same change.**\n10\t\n11\tThe contract — what \"grounded\" means, which doc to update, the deletion rule → **[`org/docs/SYNC.md`](./org/docs/SYNC.md)**. How to change things safely (add a global, a space, a provider, a tier; testing, debugging) → [`org/docs/contributing/`](./org/docs/contributing/README.md).\n12\t\n13\t## Prerequisites\n14\t\n15\t- **Node.js** ≥ 24 · **pnpm** ≥ 9 · **Git** · a GitHub account (OAuth + workspace persistence)\n16\t\n17\t## Getting Started\n18\t\n19\t```bash\n20\tpnpm install\n21\tcd sdk/org/apps/web && pnpm dev        # unified app (routes: /studio /computer /chat)\n22\t```\n23\t\n24\tFull local stack (ports, `*.test` nginx proxy, demo auth, make targets) → [`org/docs/devops/local-dev.md`](./org/docs/devops/local-dev.md).\n25\t\n26\t## Repository Structure\n27\t\n28\tThe monorepo is organized by TLD — each lmthing.\\* domain has its own top-level directory.\n29\t\n30\t```\n31\tlmthing/\n32\t├── sdk/org/            # sdk submodule (github.com/lmthing/org): runtime, shared libs, the unified web app\n33\t│   ├── libs/           # @lmthing/{auth,cli,config,core,css,state,ui,utils}\n34\t│   └── apps/web/       # unified Vite SPA; /studio, /computer, /chat as client-side routes\n35\t├── cloud/              # THE backend — Hono gateway (/api/*) + LiteLLM (/v1/*)\n36\t├── org/                # lmthing.org SPA — org/docs/** is the source of truth\n37\t├── store/              # lmthing.store SPA + the catalog (store/projects/, store/spaces/)\n38\t├── com/ social/ team/ space/ blog/ casa/     # product app shells (static SPAs)\n39\t├── devops/             # terraform, ansible, argocd, k8s manifests\n40\t```\n41\t\n42\t**There is no separate backend service.** `cloud/` is the sole backend; every frontend is a static SPA that calls it. Any server-side logic — new endpoints, DB ops, webhooks — belongs in `cloud/gateway/` or in K8s config. Detail → [`org/docs/cloud/`](./org/docs/cloud/README.md). Whole-system view (domains, pods, data flow) → [`org/docs/architecture.md`](./org/docs/architecture.md).\n43\t\n44\t## Design system — mandatory, enforced\n45\t\n46\t**Never write a raw color** in any web surface (no hex, no literal `rgb()/hsl()`, no stock Tailwind color utilities like `gray-*`/`blue-*`). Use a design token (`var(--foreground)`, `bg-primary`, …). To change a color, edit `sdk/org/libs/css/src/tokens/tokens.json` then `pnpm --filter @lmthing/css generate` — never hand-edit `theme.css`. Hard gate: `pnpm lint:tokens` (root) and CI (`.github/workflows/design-tokens.yml`) fail on violations. Rules, tokens, components → [`org/docs/design-system/`](./org/docs/design-system/README.md).\n47\t\n48\t## Task Index\n49\t\n50\tWorking on… → open the `org/docs` page that owns it.\n51\t\n52\t| Working on… | Read |\n53\t|---|---|\n54\t| **frontend styling** — tokens, Tailwind utilities, component CSS, theming (MANDATORY) | [design-system/](./org/docs/design-system/README.md) · [tokens](./org/docs/design-system/tokens.md) · [components](./org/docs/design-system/components.md) |\n55\t| **the on-disk FORMAT you author** — a project (`database/ api/ pages/ components/ hooks/ events/ spaces/`) or a space (`agents/ functions/ components/ tasklists/ knowledge/ events/`) | [format/](./org/docs/format/README.md) · [format/project/](./org/docs/format/project/README.md) · [format/space/](./org/docs/format/space/README.md) |\n56\t| **agent runtime globals** — `ask`/`display`/`fork`/`delegate`/`tasklist`, `db.*`, `writeTableSchema`/`writeApi`/`writePage`/`writeHook`, `emitEvent`, `installSpace`, `callConnection`, the capability gate | [runtime-globals/](./org/docs/runtime-globals/README.md) |\n57\t| **the core runtime** — turn/eval loop, typecheck+DTS, forks, delegation, space loading, sessions | [runtime/](./org/docs/runtime/README.md) |\n58\t| **events, hooks & integrations** — `events/*` emitter defs (webhook/cron/db/internal), event hooks, integration spaces as event sources | [format/space/events/](./org/docs/format/space/events/README.md) · [format/project/hooks/](./org/docs/format/project/hooks/README.md) · [runtime-globals/events-and-integrations](./org/docs/runtime-globals/events-and-integrations.md) |\n59\t| **the store + consent** — installing spaces/apps, `installSpace`, the consent card | [runtime-globals/store-and-consent](./org/docs/runtime-globals/store-and-consent.md) · [cli-api/rest/apps](./org/docs/cli-api/rest/apps.md) · [cli-api/rest/store-spaces](./org/docs/cli-api/rest/store-spaces.md) |\n60\t| **the `lmthing` CLI + the pod REST/WS API** — commands, flags, every `/api/*` route | [cli-api/](./org/docs/cli-api/README.md) · [cli-api/rest/](./org/docs/cli-api/rest/README.md) |\n61\t| **a product surface** — routes, features, views | [chat/](./org/docs/chat/README.md) · [studio/](./org/docs/studio/README.md) · [computer/](./org/docs/computer/README.md) · [app/](./org/docs/app/README.md) (served project-app) |\n62\t| **the backend** — gateway routes, auth/SSO/tokens, billing & tiers, LiteLLM, the render service | [cloud/](./org/docs/cloud/README.md) · [routes](./org/docs/cloud/routes.md) · [auth](./org/docs/cloud/auth.md) · [billing-and-tiers](./org/docs/cloud/billing-and-tiers.md) · [litellm](./org/docs/cloud/litellm.md) |\n63\t| **agent web search** — `webSearch`/`webFetch` and the render service | [cloud/render.md](./org/docs/cloud/render.md) |\n64\t| **shared libraries** — `@lmthing/state` (VFS), `ui`, `css`, `auth` | [libs/](./org/docs/libs/README.md) |\n65\t| **the shipped system spaces** (THING, architect, appbuilder, …) | [system-spaces/](./org/docs/system-spaces/README.md) |\n66\t| **a product SPA** (`com social team store space blog casa`) | [product-spas/](./org/docs/product-spas/README.md) |\n67\t| **infra, deploy, local stack** — k8s, ArgoCD, CI, image builds | [devops/](./org/docs/devops/README.md) · [infrastructure](./org/docs/devops/infrastructure.md) · [deploy](./org/docs/devops/deploy.md) · [local-dev](./org/docs/devops/local-dev.md) |\n68\t| **making a change** — add a global / space / provider / tier; testing, debugging | [contributing/](./org/docs/contributing/README.md) |\n69\t| **the whole system** — domain map, pod model, end-to-end data flow | [architecture.md](./org/docs/architecture.md) |\n70\t\n71\t## Kubernetes cluster (production) — practical\n72\t\n73\tUse the helpers in `devops/scripts/` — they find the SSH key, fix its permissions, and quote\n74\targuments so jsonpath braces survive the trip to the remote shell.\n75\t\n76\t```bash\n77\t./devops/scripts/cluster-ssh.sh                          # interactive shell on the node\n78\t./devops/scripts/cluster-ssh.sh 'df -h'                  # or run one command\n79\t\n80\t./devops/scripts/cluster-kubectl.sh get deployments --all-namespaces -o wide\n81\t./devops/scripts/cluster-kubectl.sh get pods -n lmthing -l app=org\n82\t\n83\t./devops/scripts/cluster-logs.sh gateway                 # follow logs (-n lmthing)\n84\t./devops/scripts/cluster-logs.sh org --tail=200\n85\t\n86\t./devops/scripts/cluster-restart.sh gateway              # restart + wait for rollout\n87\t./devops/scripts/cluster-restart.sh --all-user-pods      # blunt fallback; prompts first\n88\t```\n89\t\n90\tThe key is **terraform output, so it is gitignored** and absent from a fresh clone. The scripts search\n91\t`devops/terraform/generated/`, then `~/GEANT/lmthing/devops/terraform/generated/`, then `~/.ssh/`;\n92\toverride with `LMTHING_SSH_KEY=/path/to/key.pem` (and `LMTHING_SSH_HOST` for a different node). If none\n93\tis found, run `terraform apply` in `devops/terraform` to regenerate it.\n94\t\n95\t> Quote any kubectl arg containing `[` `]` or `{` `}` — **your local shell expands it first**\n96\t> (zsh errors with `no matches found`). `-o 'jsonpath={.items[*].metadata.name}'`, not bare.\n97\t\n98\tWhat lives in which namespace, the routing model, per-user pods and scale-to-zero → [`org/docs/devops/infrastructure.md`](./org/docs/devops/infrastructure.md).\n99\t\n100\t## Testing on production / creating a test user — practical\n101\t\n102\tThe production apps require a logged-in user. `POST https://lmthing.cloud/api/auth/register`\n103\tcreates one, but **`POST /api/auth/login` is broken** (Zitadel \"password not supported\" —\n104\tsee [.issues/zitadel-password-login-disabled.md](./.issues/zitadel-password-login-disabled.md)).\n105\tTo get a session: mint a gateway HS256 JWT with `GATEWAY_JWT_SECRET` (from the\n106\t`lmthing-secrets` k8s secret; shape in `cloud/gateway/src/lib/tokens.ts`) for the\n107\tregistered `user_id`, then inject `localStorage.lmthing_session = {accessToken,\n108\trefreshToken, expiresAt, userId, email, githubRepo:null, githubUsername:null}` on the\n109\ttarget SPA and reload. `POST /api/compute/ensure` provisions the free-tier pod;\n110\t`PUT /api/compute/env {vars}` loads API keys (it **replaces** all vars — GET + merge first;\n111\tsource keys in `sdk/org/.env`). Drive the browser with the chrome-devtools MCP.\n112\t\n113\tOpen problems live in [`.issues/`](./.issues) (CI/ArgoCD deploy flakiness, Zitadel login).\n114\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_VsdMSqwzult8golfb0xW5BYw","session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"fbe4759c-ded0-4a1f-81d3-82c36a8533c6","timestamp":"2026-07-15T23:54:51.533Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace parallel specialist persistence"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_poSjP7UquWInjnupO77rjIOT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# LMThing — Core Runtime Developer Guide (`sdk/org`)\n2\t\n3\tThe agent runtime and everything built directly on it: `@lmthing/core` (QuickJS WASM sandbox, streaming\n4\tstatement pipeline, yield protocol, spaces/forks/delegates/tasklists, typecheck, budgets), `@lmthing/cli`\n5\t(the `lmthing` binary + pod server), the shared libs, and the unified web SPA (`apps/web`).\n6\t\n7\tThe model does not call tools — **the model writes TypeScript**, one statement at a time, and the host\n8\tevaluates each statement as it streams in. A value-yielding call suspends the VM, aborts the stream, is\n9\tresolved host-side, and the results come back as a `VARIABLES` block on the next turn.\n10\t\n11\t## Source of truth — read this first\n12\t\n13\t> **[`org/docs/`](../../org/docs/README.md) (published at lmthing.org) is the single source of truth for\n14\t> this codebase.** Every factual sentence there carries a citation to the code that makes it true — a\n15\t> symbol anchor (`path#Symbol`) by preference, a line anchor (`path:Lstart-Lend`) where a symbol isn't\n16\t> appropriate. `pnpm docs:check` resolves them all as a hard CI gate. When this file disagrees with\n17\t> `org/docs`, `org/docs` wins. When `org/docs` disagrees with the **code**, the code wins and `org/docs`\n18\t> is fixed.\n19\t>\n20\t> **A change to code is not done until the matching `org/docs` page is updated in the same change.**\n21\t> The rule, the grounding convention, and the \"which doc moves with my change?\" table →\n22\t> [`org/docs/SYNC.md`](../../org/docs/SYNC.md).\n23\t\n24\tThis file is an **orientation index**: what lives here, how to run it, and where the real answer is.\n25\tKnowledge does not live here.\n26\t\n27\t## Workspace\n28\t\n29\t```bash\n30\tcd sdk/org\n31\tpnpm install                       # from lockfile\n32\tpnpm build                         # turbo run build → dist/\n33\tpnpm typecheck                     # tsc --noEmit across all packages (strict)\n34\tpnpm test                          # vitest run (co-located tests) — run from sdk/org, NOT the repo root\n35\tpnpm test libs/core/src/tasklist   # one directory / substring filter\n36\tpnpm dev                           # turbo run dev --parallel (watch + rebuild)\n37\tpnpm thing                         # CLI + web app on ONE port, both hot-reloading (scripts/thing-dev.mjs)\n38\t```\n39\t\n40\tRunning the CLI: `node libs/cli/dist/cli/bin.js --space <dir> \"<message>\"`. Keyless testing:\n41\t`--mock <file>` / `LM_MOCK=<file>` (scripted `streamFn`). `--repl` interactive · `--claude`\n42\tprogrammatic · `--web <port>` DevTools UI · `--request \"<msg>\"` headless single-shot · `--trace <file>`\n43\tNDJSON trace.\n44\t\n45\t- Every flag, subcommand and env var (model aliases, providers) → [`org/docs/cli-api/commands.md`](../../org/docs/cli-api/commands.md)\n46\t- Test runners, the two-workspace trap, the mock harness, live scenarios → [`org/docs/contributing/testing.md`](../../org/docs/contributing/testing.md)\n47\t- Debugging the eval/yield pipeline → [`org/docs/contributing/debugging.md`](../../org/docs/contributing/debugging.md)\n48\t\n49\t`.env` is read from `process.cwd()` only (`libs/cli/src/cli/bin.ts:L18`). In Claude Code web sessions\n50\tkeys are decrypted from `.env.encrypted` by `.claude/hooks/session-start.sh` — **if `TAVILY_API_KEY` or\n51\tanother secret is missing, ask for `ENV_DECRYPT_KEY` before proceeding.**\n52\t\n53\t## Layout\n54\t\n55\t`libs/{core,cli,ui,css,state,auth,utils,config}` · `libs/core/system-spaces/*` (the\n56\tshipped system + user spaces) · `apps/web` (the unified SPA — `/chat`, `/studio`, `/computer` as\n57\tclient-side routes) · `scenarios/` (live prod scenario runner).\n58\t\n59\t`@lmthing/core` never imports from `cli` or `ui` — it emits events and accepts a `RenderHost`.\n60\t\n61\tPackage-by-package detail → [`org/docs/libs/README.md`](../../org/docs/libs/README.md) · the surfaces →\n62\t[`chat/`](../../org/docs/chat/README.md) · [`studio/`](../../org/docs/studio/README.md) ·\n63\t[`computer/`](../../org/docs/computer/README.md).\n64\t\n65\t## Gotchas that bite while editing this code\n66\t\n67\tEach is one line; the grounded explanation is behind the link.\n68\t\n69\t- **Variables do not persist between evals** — each statement is its own module; the loop appends\n70\t  `globalThis['x'] = x` for every bound name. → [runtime/turn-loop](../../org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md)\n71\t- **Yield-result binding is host-side**, not the QuickJS post-`await` continuation — it maps results onto\n72\t  the binding pattern but prefers `vm.getVar(name)` where they diverge (which is what recovers a yield\n73\t  nested inside another async function). → [runtime/turn-loop](../../org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md)\n74\t- **A bridged host promise is disposed on settle, never on creation** — `resolve()`/`reject()` are no-ops\n75\t  after `dispose()`, so eager disposal permanently neuters a nested `await`. And **`vm.dispose()` must\n76\t  never throw**: it swallows QuickJS's `list_empty(&rt->gc_obj_list)` abort, which is catchable and\n77\t  benign — propagating it turns an already-produced fork result into a spurious rejection. `LM_QJS_DEBUG=1`\n78\t  loads the assertion-tracking debug WASM when hunting a real handle leak. → [runtime/](../../org/docs/runtime/README.md)\n79\t- **Not granted ⇒ not injected AND absent from the DTS** — one `CapabilityProfile` drives both, so a call\n80\t  the context cannot make fails typecheck (retryable) instead of throwing. This is why `ask`/`fork`/\n81\t  `tasklist` in a fork or delegate is a *typecheck* error. → [runtime/typecheck](../../org/docs/runtime/typecheck.md)\n82\t- **Never forbid a tool in prose — disable it in tasklist frontmatter** (`role`, `functions: [...]`,\n83\t  `canDelegateTo`); the host enforces it, prose does not.\n84\t  → [runtime/fork-and-tasklists](../../org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md) · [format/space/tasklists](../../org/docs/format/space/tasklists/README.md)\n85\t- **There is NO generic filesystem on the model surface** — `readFile`/`writeFile`/`editFile`/`listDir`/\n86\t  `glob`/`grep` and raw `execShell`/`readFileRaw`/`writeFileRaw` are absent from every agent's DTS.\n87\t  Persistence goes ONLY through typed, root-scoped writers (`writeProject*`, the architect builder\n88\t  functions); reads through `listProjectDir`/`readProjectFile` (project) or `listSpaceDir`/`readSpaceFile`\n89\t  (space). The ONE exception is the **engineer**, which holds `fs:scratch`: it keeps the generic fs/shell\n90\t  jailed to a `.lmthing/scratch/<random>` dir it must `createScratch()` first, and RETURNS code for its\n91\t  caller to persist. `readFileRaw`/`writeFileRaw` survive only as internal host primitives (memory/todos +\n92\t  architect builder bodies, which aren't typechecked against the model DTS).\n93\t  → [runtime-globals/](../../org/docs/runtime-globals/README.md)\n94\t- **Adding a worker-run seam ⇒ add its tsup entry.** Store code (space emitters, space hook handlers, code\n95\t  nodes) resolves its worker entry as a sibling of the bundled module; a missing `worker-load-entry` in\n96\t  `libs/cli/tsup.config.ts` ships an image where every emitter scan and space-hook dispatch fails in prod\n97\t  (unit tests run from `src/` and miss it). → [`libs/cli/tsup.config.ts`](./libs/cli/tsup.config.ts)\n98\t- **System spaces auto-adopt source/image updates** — a pristine materialized copy re-syncs on boot;\n99\t  locally-edited ones hold back (adopt with `--adopt-system-spaces`). → [`libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts`](./libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts) · [system-spaces/](../../org/docs/system-spaces/README.md)\n100\t- **`pnpm --filter @lmthing/core test` is a silent no-op** — core has no `test` script. Use\n101\t  `cd sdk/org && pnpm test <path>`. → [contributing/testing](../../org/docs/contributing/testing.md)\n102\t\n103\t## Rules\n104\t\n105\t- **Always test every fix.** No fix is done until a test would have caught it.\n106\t- **Update the doc in the same change.** See [`org/docs/SYNC.md`](../../org/docs/SYNC.md). If you catch\n107\t  yourself explaining behaviour *here*, it belongs in `org/docs` — put it there and link it.\n108\t- **Issue lifecycle.** File a `.issues/` entry when a bug is found; delete it when fixed and tested.\n109\t  No issue file = no known bugs. (`.issues/` is the live list — do not mirror it here.)\n110\t- **Design system is mandatory.** Any web styling uses `@lmthing/css` tokens — never a raw color. Change\n111\t  colors only via `libs/css/src/tokens/tokens.json` + `pnpm --filter @lmthing/css generate` (never\n112\t  hand-edit `theme.css`). Enforced by `lint:tokens` (hard CI gate). → [design-system/](../../org/docs/design-system/README.md)\n113\t\n114\t## Task Index\n115\t\n116\tSource of truth is the `org/docs` page. Skills (`@.claude/skills/*`) are local *procedures* only.\n117\t\n118\t| Working on… | Read |\n119\t|---|---|\n120\t| the turn loop / yield protocol / budgets / retries / prose-drop | [org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md](../../org/docs/runtime/turn-loop.md) |\n121\t| typecheck / the DTS overlay / transpile / the JSX runtime | [org/docs/runtime/typecheck.md](../../org/docs/runtime/typecheck.md) |\n122\t| forks + tasklist orchestration / roles / `forEach` / salvage / code nodes | [org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md](../../org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md) |\n123\t| `delegate()` / the registry / `canDelegateTo` / actions / auto-capture | [org/docs/runtime/delegation.md](../../org/docs/runtime/delegation.md) |\n124\t| space loading / system-space merge rules / project functions | [org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md](../../org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md) |\n125\t| the `Session` API / snapshots + resume / history summarization / tracing | [org/docs/runtime/sessions.md](../../org/docs/runtime/sessions.md) |\n126\t| a runtime global, or the capability that gates it | [org/docs/runtime-globals/](../../org/docs/runtime-globals/README.md) · procedure: `@.claude/skills/new-global.md` |\n127\t| the on-disk format of a **space** (agents, tasklists, knowledge, functions, components, events) | [org/docs/format/space/](../../org/docs/format/space/README.md) · procedure: `@.claude/skills/new-space.md` |\n128\t| the on-disk format of a **project** (`database/ api/ pages/ hooks/ events/ spaces/`) | [org/docs/format/project/](../../org/docs/format/project/README.md) |\n129\t| **project-as-application** — how an app is built, served and executed | [org/docs/app/](../../org/docs/app/README.md) · procedure: `@.claude/skills/project-app.md` |\n130\t| the `lmthing` CLI, the pod server, session persistence, `.lmthing/` | [org/docs/cli-api/](../../org/docs/cli-api/README.md) · [rest/](../../org/docs/cli-api/rest/README.md) · procedure: `@.claude/skills/project-server.md` |\n131\t| the shipped system spaces (THING, appbuilder, architect, engineer, store, …) | [org/docs/system-spaces/](../../org/docs/system-spaces/README.md) · procedure: `@.claude/skills/system-spaces.md` |\n132\t| **the unified event pipeline** — `events/*` emitter defs, event hooks, `@consent`, store globals | `@lmthing:.claude/skills/events-and-hooks.md` (repo-root skill) · [org/docs/format/space/events/](../../org/docs/format/space/events/README.md) |\n133\t| adding an AI provider | [org/docs/contributing/add-a-provider.md](../../org/docs/contributing/add-a-provider.md) |\n134\t| writing / running tests | [org/docs/contributing/testing.md](../../org/docs/contributing/testing.md) |\n135\t| debugging the eval/yield pipeline | [org/docs/contributing/debugging.md](../../org/docs/contributing/debugging.md) |\n136\t| the design system (tokens, theme, component CSS) | [org/docs/design-system/](../../org/docs/design-system/README.md) · generated CSS-class catalog: [libs/css/COMPONENTS.md](./libs/css/COMPONENTS.md) |\n137\t| the shared libs' public APIs (`state`