\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"\"}\n16\t{\"seq\":211,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"\"}\n17\t{\"seq\":212,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"\"}\n18\t{\"seq\":213,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"// Build ONE specialist: Ngorongoro Crater const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n19\t{\"seq\":214,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Ngorongoro Crater.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Ngorongoro Crater\",\"goal\":\"What are the park fees, crater-day facts, on-the-ground experiences (Emmanuel the driver, Maasai bracelet purchase, ranger tip question), and the official tariff rules that apply to Vasilis and Athina's visit?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Ngorongoro Crater\",\"executive_summary\":\"Ngorongoro Crater is the centerpiece safari day (Aug 7–9 safari window) for Vasilis and Athina Mari, a non-East African couple. It involves multiple official fees from the NCAA tariff schedule, a guided descent with driver Emmanuel, an unplanned bracelet purchase from a Maasai lady at the rim (~35,000 TZS), and an open question about a ranger tip (~5,000 TZS) that was not previously disclosed.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Official Park Fees (NCAA Tariffs, non-East African citizens)\",\"detail\":\"From the ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf and trip-costs.xlsx: Entry permit is $70.80 per non-EA adult (age 16+). Crater service fee is $70.80 per non-EA adult. Crater vehicle descent fee is $295.00 per vehicle/trip (non-EA). These three line items are reflected in the costs sheet: entry $141.60 (2 pax × $70.80), crater service fee $141.60 (2 pax × $70.80), vehicle descent $295.00. Camping fees (public campsite) are $35.40 per non-EA adult 16+; special campsite is $70.80. However Vasilis's safari package uses Jevas Hotel (HB) at the rim, not camping inside the crater. Only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight are allowed on the crater floor. Crater descent gates close at 16:00; all visitors must exit by 18:00. Speed limit is 25 kph at the crater. A licensed guide or NCAA ranger must accompany all crater visitors. Off-road driving is prohibited. A maximum of 5 vehicles at an animal sighting. Ngorongoro nights are cold — warm layers needed (per markdown notes).\"},{\"heading\":\"Crater-Day Experience (Voice Memo + Specialist Facts)\",\"detail\":\"The crater day was described as 'one of the best days of my life' — wildlife everywhere, up close. The driver/guide was Emmanuel (not Richard from the Suricata office), described as very knowledgeable, spotting wildlife before they even came into view. At the rim, on the way out, a Maasai lady was selling beaded bracelets. Vasilis bought two for Athina Mari. The asking price was $25 or $20 for both (uncertain recall); he paid roughly 35,000 TZS in shillings. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip expected at the gate: ~5,000 TZS cash, separate from park fees — something nobody told them about beforehand.\"},{\"heading\":\"Open Questions / Reminders\",\"detail\":\"Ask Richard whether the ranger tip (~5,000 TZS) is legitimate/expected, before settling the safari balance payment ($960 USD). The exact bracelet purchase amount is uncertain (roughly 35,000 TZS ≈ $20–25 USD); should be recorded as an estimated expense with a note. NCAA rules: only designated Cultural Bomas permit photography of local people; the Maasai bracelet purchase at the rim may fall outside that — worth noting.\"},{\"heading\":\"Ngorongoro Contacts & Resources\",\"detail\":\"Ngorongoro Information Office: +255 734 160 014 / +255 734 160 015. Karatu Information Office: +255 27 253 4068. Email: cc@ncaa.go.tz. Web: www.ncaa.go.tz. Conservation Commissioner, NCAA, P.O. Box 1, Ngorongoro Crater, Arusha. Hotline: +255 27 253 7046.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"The Ngorongoro day is fully costed at $578.20 in official fees (entry + service + vehicle descent for 2 pax), with Jevas Hotel providing overnight lodging on the rim (included in the Suricata package). The two open items are the ~35,000 TZS bracelet purchase (estimate) and the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip question — both need confirmation and recording in the trip app.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n20\t{\"seq\":215,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n21\t{\"seq\":216,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n22\t{\"seq\":217,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"\"}\n23\t{\"seq\":218,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"\"}\n24\t{\"seq\":219,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"// Build the Stone Town / Zanzibar specialist space from the inventoried scope. // Delegating directly to the system architect with the item's topic, goal, and research. const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n25\t{\"seq\":220,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Stone Town / Zanzibar.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Stone Town / Zanzibar\",\"goal\":\"What are the Zanzibar leg details: Stone Town lodging, beach stay, The Rock Restaurant dinner, local driving permit requirements, and the visual character of Stone Town from the courtyard photo?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Stone Town / Zanzibar\",\"executive_summary\":\"The Zanzibar leg runs Aug 11–17, split between Stone Town (2 nights at Treasures of Zanzibar House) and Kiwengwa beach (4 nights at Ayla Beach House). It includes a fully booked dinner at The Rock Restaurant on Aug 15, a local driving permit requirement, and the classic Stone Town architectural character captured in the courtyard photo.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Lodging & Dates\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 11–13: Stone Town — Treasures of Zanzibar House, 2 nights, $100 total. Aug 13–17: Kiwengwa beach — Ayla Beach House, 4 nights, $304 total. Flight arrives in Zanzibar (ZNZ) on Aug 11 via Precision Air TC145 at 13:40. Departure to Dar es Salaam is Aug 17 (ferry, per markdown notes).\"},{\"heading\":\"The Rock Restaurant Dinner\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00 sitting, 2 adults, 2× Tropical Passion Fruit Cheesecake included. Fully paid ($46 total). Outdoor seating requested for sunset/star views. Contacts: +255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com.\"},{\"heading\":\"Local Driving Permit\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Vasilis holds an International Driving Permit (IDP). A local Zanzibar Driving Permit is also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months, cost from spreadsheet: $15). Most rental companies arrange this with a license photo provided 24+ hours before arrival. Police checkpoints are frequent; carry both IDP and local permit (screenshot acceptable).\"},{\"heading\":\"Stone Town Visual Character (Photo Facts)\",\"detail\":\"From specialistFacts (image description): The Stone Town photo shows a bright, upward-looking courtyard or hotel atrium with whitewashed walls, arched windows, and dark carved wooden balconies stacked several stories high. Sunny, airy mood under a clear sky. Classic Stone Town architecture — this is likely the Treasures of Zanzibar House or a nearby courtyard typical of the historic district.\"},{\"heading\":\"Swimming & Beach Notes\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md: For Zanzibar swimming, the north coast (Nungwi area) offers more consistent conditions vs. east/south coasts where low tide limits access. Kiwengwa is on the east coast, so tide-dependent swimming should be expected. The markdown recommends north-coast beaches for better water access.\"},{\"heading\":\"Zanzibar Mandatory Insurance\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: Zanzibar requires separate mandatory travel insurance from the Zanzibar Insurance Corporation (ZIC). Cost is $44 per traveler, $88 total for both — listed in the costs sheet.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"Zanzibar is a 6-night split stay combining cultural Stone Town and beach relaxation in Kiwengwa, anchored by a confirmed dinner at The Rock on Aug 15. The local driving permit (~$15) and Zanzibar insurance ($88) are mandatory add-ons. Swimming is tide-dependent on the east coast. The photo captures the classic Stone Town aesthetic: whitewashed, arched, and wooden-balconied.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n26\t{\"seq\":221,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n27\t{\"seq\":222,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n28\t{\"seq\":223,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"\"}\n29\t{\"seq\":224,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"\"}\n30\t{\"seq\":225,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"// I'm being asked to build a specialist space for \\\"Cairo Stopovers\\\" using the research that's already provided. // The item contains the research findings directly. I delegate to the architect with this fully-formed scope. const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n31\t{\"seq\":226,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Cairo Stopovers.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Cairo Stopovers\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of both Cairo stopovers: hotels, sightseeing plans, flights, and costs?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Cairo Stopovers\",\"executive_summary\":\"Cairo features twice in the itinerary as arrival and departure stopovers, anchoring the whole trip. Stopover 1 (Aug 3–5) includes the Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza. Stopover 2 (Aug 19–20) covers Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, and Coptic Cairo. Both legs are fully booked with distinct hotels.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Stopover 1 — Arrival (Aug 3–5)\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Hotel: Eileen Hotel, Cairo — Aug 3–5, 2 nights, $102 total. Address: 21 Youssef El-Gendy St, Abdeen, Downtown Cairo (near Tahrir Square). Phone: +20 15 56434043, email: info@eileenhotel.com. Flight in: ATH→CAI, Aegean A3932, Aug 3, 06:55–08:50, ref ZZJQUU. Flight out: CAI→DAR, EgyptAir, Aug 4, 22:40–04:20+1. Sightseeing plan: Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza. Note: late checkout Aug 5 is noted but not used for sleep since flight departs late on Aug 4.\"},{\"heading\":\"Stopover 2 — Departure (Aug 19–20)\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Hotel: Ramses Hilton, Cairo — Aug 19–20, 1 night, $87 total. Flight in: DAR→CAI, EgyptAir, Aug 19, 05:20–11:05. Flight out: CAI→ATH, Aegean A3935, Aug 20, 19:55–22:00, ref ZZL22S. Sightseeing plan: Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, Coptic Cairo. Taxi needed between Citadel and Coptic Cairo.\"},{\"heading\":\"Egypt E-Visa Requirement\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: Egypt e-visa is multiple-entry, $65 per person, $130 total for both travelers. Each traveler applies separately. A printed copy is mandatory.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"Cairo bookends the trip with two distinct 2-day/1-night stays. The first is museum-and-pyramids focused from a downtown base; the second is a whirlwind historical Cairo tour from the Ramses Hilton. Both require the same multiple-entry e-visa ($130 total, printed copy required). Combined lodging cost is $189.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n32\t{\"seq\":227,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n33\t{\"seq\":228,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n34\t{\"seq\":229,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"\"}\n35\t{\"seq\":230,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"\"}\n36\t{\"seq\":231,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"// Build Safari Logistics specialist from the inventoried scope. // We have all the source material in the item already — no external research needed. // Delegate directly to the architect with the pre-researched item. const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n37\t{\"seq\":232,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Safari Logistics.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of the 3-day Suricata Safaris camping safari: contacts (Richard), payment schedule, vehicle requirements, itinerary, and the Arusha lodging that frames the safari?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"executive_summary\":\"The safari is a 3-day group camping safari (Aug 7–9) operated by Suricata Safaris Ltd, contact Richard. It covers Tarangire NP, Lake Manyara NP, and Ngorongoro Crater, with overnight at Twiga Camp Site and Jevas Hotel. Total cost is $1,200 with a $240 deposit paid and $960 balance due on arrival. Arusha serves as the logistical base with pre- and post-safari hotel stays.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Operator & Contact\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Suricata Safaris Ltd — Richard, phone: +255 763 222 293, email: info@suricatasafaris.com. The driver/guide at Ngorongoro was Emmanuel (not Richard), indicating Suricata uses multiple driver-guides. Richard appears to be the office/logistics contact.\"},{\"heading\":\"Itinerary & Accommodations\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 7–9, 3-day group camping safari. Day 1: Tarangire National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB — full board). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater → overnight Jevas Hotel (HB — half board). Park fees are separate from the safari package: Tarangire entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Lake Manyara entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Ngorongoro fees $578.20 total (entry $141.60 + crater service $141.60 + vehicle descent $295). These park fees total $814.20 and are listed separately in the costs sheet, meaning the $1,200 safari package likely covers guide, vehicle, camping gear, and meals but excludes park fees — or the breakdown in costs splits them for tracking.\"},{\"heading\":\"Payment Schedule\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Total safari cost: $1,200. Deposit paid (20%): $240. Balance due: $960. Payment method: cash on arrival (USD, post-2009 notes only) OR online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Cash is preferred to avoid the 5% surcharge ($48 extra).\"},{\"heading\":\"Vehicle Information\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and NCAA tariffs: Suricata Safaris provides a 4×4 safari vehicle (required for Ngorongoro Crater descent — only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight allowed on crater floor). The vehicle must be a registered company vehicle with a valid TALA license per Tourism Act No. 29, 2008. The NCAA vehicle descent fee is $295 per trip (non-EA registered).\"},{\"heading\":\"Arusha Base (Pre- and Post-Safari)\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Aug 5–7: Serengeti Villa, Arusha, 2 nights, $62 total. Phone: +255 757 757 928. Aug 9–11: Kutoka Lodge, Arusha, 2 nights, $96 total. These frame the safari and serve as staging/rest points. Flight ARK arrival Aug 5 at 12:00 (Precision Air TC144); departure ARK→ZNZ Aug 11 at 12:40 (Precision Air TC145).\"},{\"heading\":\"Park Fees Summary (Excluded from Safari Package?)\",\"detail\":\"From trip-costs.xlsx costs sheet, park fees are listed as separate line items totaling $814.20: Tarangire $118 + Lake Manyara $118 + Ngorongoro entry $141.60 + Ngorongoro crater service $141.60 + Ngorongoro vehicle descent $295. The safari package ($1,200) may or may not include these — the costs sheet lists them independently but doesn't clarify whether Richard's package covers them. This is worth confirming with Richard alongside the ranger tip question.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"The 3-day Suricata Safaris package is the operational backbone of the Tanzania leg, with Richard as the key contact. The $960 balance (cash, post-2009 USD) is the largest outstanding payment. Two open questions for Richard: (1) is the ranger tip legitimate/expected? (2) are the listed park fees included in the $1,200 package or additional? Arusha provides comfortable bookend stays at Serengeti Villa and Kutoka Lodge.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n38\t{\"seq\":233,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n39\t{\"seq\":234,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n40\t{\"seq\":235,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — run the synthesis\"}\n41\t{\"seq\":236,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n42\t{\"seq\":237,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n43\t{\"seq\":238,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 —\"}\n44\t{\"seq\":239,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n45\t{\"seq\":240,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n46\t{\"seq\":241,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"// Turn\"}\n47\t{\"seq\":242,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n48\t{\"seq\":243,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n49\t{\"seq\":244,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — run the build\"}\n50\t{\"seq\":245,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n51\t{\"seq\":246,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n52\t{\"seq\":247,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n53\t{\"seq\":248,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n54\t{\"seq\":249,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — seed the build pipeline with the research already handed to us in context. // No deep-research; synthesize_and_run builds (design → write → validate → register) inside the tasklist. const t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', { topic: context.topic, goal: context.goal, research: JSON.stringify(context.research), });\"}\n55\t{\"seq\":250,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"tasklist\",\"args\":[\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of the 3-day Suricata Safaris camping safari: contacts (Richard), payment schedule, vehicle requirements, itinerary, and the Arusha lodging that frames the safari?\",\"research\":\"{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Safari Logistics\\\",\\\"executive_summary\\\":\\\"The safari is a 3-day group camping safari (Aug 7–9) operated by Suricata Safaris Ltd, contact Richard. It covers Tarangire NP, Lake Manyara NP, and Ngorongoro Crater, with overnight at Twiga Camp Site and Jevas Hotel. Total cost is $1,200 with a $240 deposit paid and $960 balance due on arrival. Arusha serves as the logistical base with pre- and post-safari hotel stays.\\\",\\\"findings\\\":[{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Operator & Contact\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Suricata Safaris Ltd — Richard, phone: +255 763 222 293, email: info@suricatasafaris.com. The driver/guide at Ngorongoro was Emmanuel (not Richard), indicating Suricata uses multiple driver-guides. Richard appears to be the office/logistics contact.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Itinerary & Accommodations\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 7–9, 3-day group camping safari. Day 1: Tarangire National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB — full board). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater → overnight Jevas Hotel (HB — half board). Park fees are separate from the safari package: Tarangire entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Lake Manyara entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Ngorongoro fees $578.20 total (entry $141.60 + crater service $141.60 + vehicle descent $295). These park fees total $814.20 and are listed separately in the costs sheet, meaning the $1,200 safari package likely covers guide, vehicle, camping gear, and meals but excludes park fees — or the breakdown in costs splits them for tracking.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Payment Schedule\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Total safari cost: $1,200. Deposit paid (20%): $240. Balance due: $960. Payment method: cash on arrival (USD, post-2009 notes only) OR online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Cash is preferred to avoid the 5% surcharge ($48 extra).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Vehicle Information\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and NCAA tariffs: Suricata Safaris provides a 4×4 safari vehicle (required for Ngorongoro Crater descent — only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight allowed on crater floor). The vehicle must be a registered company vehicle with a valid TALA license per Tourism Act No. 29, 2008. The NCAA vehicle descent fee is $295 per trip (non-EA registered).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Arusha Base (Pre- and Post-Safari)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Aug 5–7: Serengeti Villa, Arusha, 2 nights, $62 total. Phone: +255 757 757 928. Aug 9–11: Kutoka Lodge, Arusha, 2 nights, $96 total. These frame the safari and serve as staging/rest points. Flight ARK arrival Aug 5 at 12:00 (Precision Air TC144); departure ARK→ZNZ Aug 11 at 12:40 (Precision Air TC145).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Park Fees Summary (Excluded from Safari Package?)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From trip-costs.xlsx costs sheet, park fees are listed as separate line items totaling $814.20: Tarangire $118 + Lake Manyara $118 + Ngorongoro entry $141.60 + Ngorongoro crater service $141.60 + Ngorongoro vehicle descent $295. The safari package ($1,200) may or may not include these — the costs sheet lists them independently but doesn't clarify whether Richard's package covers them. This is worth confirming with Richard alongside the ranger tip question.\\\"}],\\\"conclusion\\\":\\\"The 3-day Suricata Safaris package is the operational backbone of the Tanzania leg, with Richard as the key contact. The $960 balance (cash, post-2009 USD) is the largest outstanding payment. Two open questions for Richard: (1) is the ranger tip legitimate/expected? (2) are the listed park fees included in the $1,200 package or additional? Arusha provides comfortable bookend stays at Serengeti Villa and Kutoka Lodge.\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[]}\"}]}\n56\t{\"seq\":251,\"type\":\"yield_resolved\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"tasklist\"}\n57\t{\"seq\":252,\"type\":\"variables\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n58\t{\"seq\":253,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n59\t{\"seq\":254,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n60\t{\"seq\":255,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n61\t{\"seq\":256,\"type\":\"typecheck_error\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"Cannot find name 't'.\"}\n62\t{\"seq\":257,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"// Turn 2 — report the build result const built = t.data as { spaceKey: string; agentSlug: string; actionId: string; query: string; ok: boolean; errors: string }; const\"}\n63\t{\"seq\":258,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n64\t{\"seq\":259,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n65\t{\"seq\":260,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n66\t{\"seq\":261,\"type\":\"typecheck_error\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"Cannot find name 't'.\"}\n67\t{\"seq\":262,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"// Turn 2 — Report the build result from the tasklist that ran in Turn 1. // `t` is the result of the synthesize_and_run tasklist. const built = t.data as { spaceKey: string; agentSlug: string; actionId: string; query: string; ok: boolean; errors: string };\"}\n68\t{\"seq\":263,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n69\t{\"seq\":264,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n70\t{\"seq\":265,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n71\t{\"seq\":266,\"type\":\"typecheck_error\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"Cannot find name 't'.\"}\n72\t{\"seq\":267,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"// The tasklist `synthesize_and_run` has already resolved. The result `t` is bound and contains the build outcome. // Turn 2 — extract the payload and report the final result. // We must reference the already-bound variable `t` from the previous turn. // The payload is in t.data; we build the final response from it. const built = (t as any).data as { spaceKey: string; agentSlug: string; actionId: string; query: string; ok: boolean; errors: string };\"}\n73\t{\"seq\":268,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n74\t{\"seq\":269,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n75\t{\"seq\":270,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n76\t{\"seq\":271,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — run the synthesis pipeline seeded with the research from context const t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', { topic: context.topic, goal: context.goal, research: JSON.stringify(context.research), });\"}\n77\t{\"seq\":272,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"tasklist\",\"args\":[\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"topic\":\"Stone Town / Zanzibar\",\"goal\":\"What are the Zanzibar leg details: Stone Town lodging, beach stay, The Rock Restaurant dinner, local driving permit requirements, and the visual character of Stone Town from the courtyard photo?\",\"research\":\"{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Stone Town / Zanzibar\\\",\\\"executive_summary\\\":\\\"The Zanzibar leg runs Aug 11–17, split between Stone Town (2 nights at Treasures of Zanzibar House) and Kiwengwa beach (4 nights at Ayla Beach House). It includes a fully booked dinner at The Rock Restaurant on Aug 15, a local driving permit requirement, and the classic Stone Town architectural character captured in the courtyard photo.\\\",\\\"findings\\\":[{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Lodging & Dates\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 11–13: Stone Town — Treasures of Zanzibar House, 2 nights, $100 total. Aug 13–17: Kiwengwa beach — Ayla Beach House, 4 nights, $304 total. Flight arrives in Zanzibar (ZNZ) on Aug 11 via Precision Air TC145 at 13:40. Departure to Dar es Salaam is Aug 17 (ferry, per markdown notes).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"The Rock Restaurant Dinner\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00 sitting, 2 adults, 2× Tropical Passion Fruit Cheesecake included. Fully paid ($46 total). Outdoor seating requested for sunset/star views. Contacts: +255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Local Driving Permit\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Vasilis holds an International Driving Permit (IDP). A local Zanzibar Driving Permit is also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months, cost from spreadsheet: $15). Most rental companies arrange this with a license photo provided 24+ hours before arrival. Police checkpoints are frequent; carry both IDP and local permit (screenshot acceptable).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Stone Town Visual Character (Photo Facts)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From specialistFacts (image description): The Stone Town photo shows a bright, upward-looking courtyard or hotel atrium with whitewashed walls, arched windows, and dark carved wooden balconies stacked several stories high. Sunny, airy mood under a clear sky. Classic Stone Town architecture — this is likely the Treasures of Zanzibar House or a nearby courtyard typical of the historic district.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Swimming & Beach Notes\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md: For Zanzibar swimming, the north coast (Nungwi area) offers more consistent conditions vs. east/south coasts where low tide limits access. Kiwengwa is on the east coast, so tide-dependent swimming should be expected. The markdown recommends north-coast beaches for better water access.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Zanzibar Mandatory Insurance\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: Zanzibar requires separate mandatory travel insurance from the Zanzibar Insurance Corporation (ZIC). Cost is $44 per traveler, $88 total for both — listed in the costs sheet.\\\"}],\\\"conclusion\\\":\\\"Zanzibar is a 6-night split stay combining cultural Stone Town and beach relaxation in Kiwengwa, anchored by a confirmed dinner at The Rock on Aug 15. The local driving permit (~$15) and Zanzibar insurance ($88) are mandatory add-ons. Swimming is tide-dependent on the east coast. The photo captures the classic Stone Town aesthetic: whitewashed, arched, and wooden-balconied.\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[]}\"}]}\n78\t{\"seq\":273,\"type\":\"yield_resolved\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"tasklist\"}\n79\t{\"seq\":274,\"type\":\"variables\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n80\t{\"seq\":275,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n81\t{\"seq\":276,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n82\t{\"seq\":277,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n83\t{\"seq\":278,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n84\t{\"seq\":279,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n85\t{\"seq\":280,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — run the build pipeline with the context already provided. const t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', { topic: context.topic, goal: context.goal, research: JSON.stringify(context.research), });\"}\n86\t{\"seq\":281,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"tasklist\",\"args\":[\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"topic\":\"Ngorongoro Crater\",\"goal\":\"What are the park fees, crater-day facts, on-the-ground experiences (Emmanuel the driver, Maasai bracelet purchase, ranger tip question), and the official tariff rules that apply to Vasilis and Athina's visit?\",\"research\":\"{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro Crater\\\",\\\"executive_summary\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro Crater is the centerpiece safari day (Aug 7–9 safari window) for Vasilis and Athina Mari, a non-East African couple. It involves multiple official fees from the NCAA tariff schedule, a guided descent with driver Emmanuel, an unplanned bracelet purchase from a Maasai lady at the rim (~35,000 TZS), and an open question about a ranger tip (~5,000 TZS) that was not previously disclosed.\\\",\\\"findings\\\":[{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Official Park Fees (NCAA Tariffs, non-East African citizens)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From the ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf and trip-costs.xlsx: Entry permit is $70.80 per non-EA adult (age 16+). Crater service fee is $70.80 per non-EA adult. Crater vehicle descent fee is $295.00 per vehicle/trip (non-EA). These three line items are reflected in the costs sheet: entry $141.60 (2 pax × $70.80), crater service fee $141.60 (2 pax × $70.80), vehicle descent $295.00. Camping fees (public campsite) are $35.40 per non-EA adult 16+; special campsite is $70.80. However Vasilis's safari package uses Jevas Hotel (HB) at the rim, not camping inside the crater. Only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight are allowed on the crater floor. Crater descent gates close at 16:00; all visitors must exit by 18:00. Speed limit is 25 kph at the crater. A licensed guide or NCAA ranger must accompany all crater visitors. Off-road driving is prohibited. A maximum of 5 vehicles at an animal sighting. Ngorongoro nights are cold — warm layers needed (per markdown notes).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Crater-Day Experience (Voice Memo + Specialist Facts)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"The crater day was described as 'one of the best days of my life' — wildlife everywhere, up close. The driver/guide was Emmanuel (not Richard from the Suricata office), described as very knowledgeable, spotting wildlife before they even came into view. At the rim, on the way out, a Maasai lady was selling beaded bracelets. Vasilis bought two for Athina Mari. The asking price was $25 or $20 for both (uncertain recall); he paid roughly 35,000 TZS in shillings. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip expected at the gate: ~5,000 TZS cash, separate from park fees — something nobody told them about beforehand.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Open Questions / Reminders\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"Ask Richard whether the ranger tip (~5,000 TZS) is legitimate/expected, before settling the safari balance payment ($960 USD). The exact bracelet purchase amount is uncertain (roughly 35,000 TZS ≈ $20–25 USD); should be recorded as an estimated expense with a note. NCAA rules: only designated Cultural Bomas permit photography of local people; the Maasai bracelet purchase at the rim may fall outside that — worth noting.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro Contacts & Resources\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro Information Office: +255 734 160 014 / +255 734 160 015. Karatu Information Office: +255 27 253 4068. Email: cc@ncaa.go.tz. Web: www.ncaa.go.tz. Conservation Commissioner, NCAA, P.O. Box 1, Ngorongoro Crater, Arusha. Hotline: +255 27 253 7046.\\\"}],\\\"conclusion\\\":\\\"The Ngorongoro day is fully costed at $578.20 in official fees (entry + service + vehicle descent for 2 pax), with Jevas Hotel providing overnight lodging on the rim (included in the Suricata package). The two open items are the ~35,000 TZS bracelet purchase (estimate) and the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip question — both need confirmation and recording in the trip app.\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[]}\"}]}\n87\t{\"seq\":282,\"type\":\"yield_resolved\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"tasklist\"}\n88\t{\"seq\":283,\"type\":\"variables\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n89\t{\"seq\":284,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n90\t{\"seq\":285,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n91\t{\"seq\":286,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n92\t{\"seq\":287,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"// t is undefined — the tasklist call errored or returned nothing. Let me check what happened. // The seed variable is `context` which holds `{ topic, goal, research }`. Let me re-run with explicit values. const ctx = context as { topic: string; goal: string; research: any }; const t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', { topic: ctx.topic, goal: ctx.goal, research: JSON.stringify(ctx.research), });\"}\n93\t{\"seq\":288,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"tasklist\",\"args\":[\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of the 3-day Suricata Safaris camping safari: contacts (Richard), payment schedule, vehicle requirements, itinerary, and the Arusha lodging that frames the safari?\",\"research\":\"{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Safari Logistics\\\",\\\"executive_summary\\\":\\\"The safari is a 3-day group camping safari (Aug 7–9) operated by Suricata Safaris Ltd, contact Richard. It covers Tarangire NP, Lake Manyara NP, and Ngorongoro Crater, with overnight at Twiga Camp Site and Jevas Hotel. Total cost is $1,200 with a $240 deposit paid and $960 balance due on arrival. Arusha serves as the logistical base with pre- and post-safari hotel stays.\\\",\\\"findings\\\":[{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Operator & Contact\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Suricata Safaris Ltd — Richard, phone: +255 763 222 293, email: info@suricatasafaris.com. The driver/guide at Ngorongoro was Emmanuel (not Richard), indicating Suricata uses multiple driver-guides. Richard appears to be the office/logistics contact.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Itinerary & Accommodations\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 7–9, 3-day group camping safari. Day 1: Tarangire National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB — full board). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater → overnight Jevas Hotel (HB — half board). Park fees are separate from the safari package: Tarangire entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Lake Manyara entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Ngorongoro fees $578.20 total (entry $141.60 + crater service $141.60 + vehicle descent $295). These park fees total $814.20 and are listed separately in the costs sheet, meaning the $1,200 safari package likely covers guide, vehicle, camping gear, and meals but excludes park fees — or the breakdown in costs splits them for tracking.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Payment Schedule\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Total safari cost: $1,200. Deposit paid (20%): $240. Balance due: $960. Payment method: cash on arrival (USD, post-2009 notes only) OR online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Cash is preferred to avoid the 5% surcharge ($48 extra).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Vehicle Information\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and NCAA tariffs: Suricata Safaris provides a 4×4 safari vehicle (required for Ngorongoro Crater descent — only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight allowed on crater floor). The vehicle must be a registered company vehicle with a valid TALA license per Tourism Act No. 29, 2008. The NCAA vehicle descent fee is $295 per trip (non-EA registered).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Arusha Base (Pre- and Post-Safari)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Aug 5–7: Serengeti Villa, Arusha, 2 nights, $62 total. Phone: +255 757 757 928. Aug 9–11: Kutoka Lodge, Arusha, 2 nights, $96 total. These frame the safari and serve as staging/rest points. Flight ARK arrival Aug 5 at 12:00 (Precision Air TC144); departure ARK→ZNZ Aug 11 at 12:40 (Precision Air TC145).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Park Fees Summary (Excluded from Safari Package?)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From trip-costs.xlsx costs sheet, park fees are listed as separate line items totaling $814.20: Tarangire $118 + Lake Manyara $118 + Ngorongoro entry $141.60 + Ngorongoro crater service $141.60 + Ngorongoro vehicle descent $295. The safari package ($1,200) may or may not include these — the costs sheet lists them independently but doesn't clarify whether Richard's package covers them. This is worth confirming with Richard alongside the ranger tip question.\\\"}],\\\"conclusion\\\":\\\"The 3-day Suricata Safaris package is the operational backbone of the Tanzania leg, with Richard as the key contact. The $960 balance (cash, post-2009 USD) is the largest outstanding payment. Two open questions for Richard: (1) is the ranger tip legitimate/expected? (2) are the listed park fees included in the $1,200 package or additional? Arusha provides comfortable bookend stays at Serengeti Villa and Kutoka Lodge.\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[]}\"}]}\n94\t{\"seq\":289,\"type\":\"yield_resolved\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"tasklist\"}\n95\t{\"seq\":290,\"type\":\"variables\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n96\t{\"seq\":291,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n97\t{\"seq\":292,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n98\t{\"seq\":293,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n99\t{\"seq\":294,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"currentTask.resolve({ ok: false, error: 'Tasklist synthesize_and_run returned undefined — the space directory may not exist yet or the tasklist failed before producing a result. Check that a space for Ngorongoro Crater has been scaffolded.' });\"}\n100\t{\"seq\":295,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"69c53094-b5b6-4eb4-98f9-31920b56966f","timestamp":"2026-07-15T23:55:50.464Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/tanzania-architect-compact.jsonl","content":"{\"seq\":188,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"task_10_420b1041\",\"text\":\"task\"}\n{\"seq\":189,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist[0]\",\"nodeId\":\"task_11_30811b2b\",\"text\":\"task\"}\n{\"seq\":190,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"fork\"}\n{\"seq\":192,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist[1]\",\"nodeId\":\"task_13_1ea84c10\",\"text\":\"task\"}\n{\"seq\":193,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"fork\"}\n{\"seq\":195,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist[2]\",\"nodeId\":\"task_15_698acdd6\",\"text\":\"task\"}\n{\"seq\":196,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"fork\"}\n{\"seq\":198,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist[3]\",\"nodeId\":\"task_17_15e9c548\",\"text\":\"task\"}\n{\"seq\":199,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"fork\"}\n{\"seq\":201,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist[4]\",\"nodeId\":\"task_19_321aeb97\",\"text\":\"task\"}\n{\"seq\":202,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_20_fce6e5ec\",\"text\":\"fork\"}\n{\"seq\":207,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":208,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":209,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":210,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":211,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":212,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":213,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"// Build ONE specialist: Ngorongoro Crater const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n{\"seq\":214,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_12_7ffc121e\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Ngorongoro Crater.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Ngorongoro Crater\",\"goal\":\"What are the park fees, crater-day facts, on-the-ground experiences (Emmanuel the driver, Maasai bracelet purchase, ranger tip question), and the official tariff rules that apply to Vasilis and Athina's visit?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Ngorongoro Crater\",\"executive_summary\":\"Ngorongoro Crater is the centerpiece safari day (Aug 7–9 safari window) for Vasilis and Athina Mari, a non-East African couple. It involves multiple official fees from the NCAA tariff schedule, a guided descent with driver Emmanuel, an unplanned bracelet purchase from a Maasai lady at the rim (~35,000 TZS), and an open question about a ranger tip (~5,000 TZS) that was not previously disclosed.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Official Park Fees (NCAA Tariffs, non-East African citizens)\",\"detail\":\"From the ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf and trip-costs.xlsx: Entry permit is $70.80 per non-EA adult (age 16+). Crater service fee is $70.80 per non-EA adult. Crater vehicle descent fee is $295.00 per vehicle/trip (non-EA). These three line items are reflected in the costs sheet: entry $141.60 (2 pax × $70.80), crater service fee $141.60 (2 pax × $70.80), vehicle descent $295.00. Camping fees (public campsite) are $35.40 per non-EA adult 16+; special campsite is $70.80. However Vasilis's safari package uses Jevas Hotel (HB) at the rim, not camping inside the crater. Only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight are allowed on the crater floor. Crater descent gates close at 16:00; all visitors must exit by 18:00. Speed limit is 25 kph at the crater. A licensed guide or NCAA ranger must accompany all crater visitors. Off-road driving is prohibited. A maximum of 5 vehicles at an animal sighting. Ngorongoro nights are cold — warm layers needed (per markdown notes).\"},{\"heading\":\"Crater-Day Experience (Voice Memo + Specialist Facts)\",\"detail\":\"The crater day was described as 'one of the best days of my life' — wildlife everywhere, up close. The driver/guide was Emmanuel (not Richard from the Suricata office), described as very knowledgeable, spotting wildlife before they even came into view. At the rim, on the way out, a Maasai lady was selling beaded bracelets. Vasilis bought two for Athina Mari. The asking price was $25 or $20 for both (uncertain recall); he paid roughly 35,000 TZS in shillings. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip expected at the gate: ~5,000 TZS cash, separate from park fees — something nobody told them about beforehand.\"},{\"heading\":\"Open Questions / Reminders\",\"detail\":\"Ask Richard whether the ranger tip (~5,000 TZS) is legitimate/expected, before settling the safari balance payment ($960 USD). The exact bracelet purchase amount is uncertain (roughly 35,000 TZS ≈ $20–25 USD); should be recorded as an estimated expense with a note. NCAA rules: only designated Cultural Bomas permit photography of local people; the Maasai bracelet purchase at the rim may fall outside that — worth noting.\"},{\"heading\":\"Ngorongoro Contacts & Resources\",\"detail\":\"Ngorongoro Information Office: +255 734 160 014 / +255 734 160 015. Karatu Information Office: +255 27 253 4068. Email: cc@ncaa.go.tz. Web: www.ncaa.go.tz. Conservation Commissioner, NCAA, P.O. Box 1, Ngorongoro Crater, Arusha. Hotline: +255 27 253 7046.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"The Ngorongoro day is fully costed at $578.20 in official fees (entry + service + vehicle descent for 2 pax), with Jevas Hotel providing overnight lodging on the rim (included in the Suricata package). The two open items are the ~35,000 TZS bracelet purchase (estimate) and the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip question — both need confirmation and recording in the trip app.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n{\"seq\":215,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n{\"seq\":216,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":217,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":218,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":219,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"// Build the Stone Town / Zanzibar specialist space from the inventoried scope. // Delegating directly to the system architect with the item's topic, goal, and research. const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n{\"seq\":220,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_14_bdb9b263\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Stone Town / Zanzibar.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Stone Town / Zanzibar\",\"goal\":\"What are the Zanzibar leg details: Stone Town lodging, beach stay, The Rock Restaurant dinner, local driving permit requirements, and the visual character of Stone Town from the courtyard photo?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Stone Town / Zanzibar\",\"executive_summary\":\"The Zanzibar leg runs Aug 11–17, split between Stone Town (2 nights at Treasures of Zanzibar House) and Kiwengwa beach (4 nights at Ayla Beach House). It includes a fully booked dinner at The Rock Restaurant on Aug 15, a local driving permit requirement, and the classic Stone Town architectural character captured in the courtyard photo.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Lodging & Dates\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 11–13: Stone Town — Treasures of Zanzibar House, 2 nights, $100 total. Aug 13–17: Kiwengwa beach — Ayla Beach House, 4 nights, $304 total. Flight arrives in Zanzibar (ZNZ) on Aug 11 via Precision Air TC145 at 13:40. Departure to Dar es Salaam is Aug 17 (ferry, per markdown notes).\"},{\"heading\":\"The Rock Restaurant Dinner\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00 sitting, 2 adults, 2× Tropical Passion Fruit Cheesecake included. Fully paid ($46 total). Outdoor seating requested for sunset/star views. Contacts: +255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com.\"},{\"heading\":\"Local Driving Permit\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Vasilis holds an International Driving Permit (IDP). A local Zanzibar Driving Permit is also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months, cost from spreadsheet: $15). Most rental companies arrange this with a license photo provided 24+ hours before arrival. Police checkpoints are frequent; carry both IDP and local permit (screenshot acceptable).\"},{\"heading\":\"Stone Town Visual Character (Photo Facts)\",\"detail\":\"From specialistFacts (image description): The Stone Town photo shows a bright, upward-looking courtyard or hotel atrium with whitewashed walls, arched windows, and dark carved wooden balconies stacked several stories high. Sunny, airy mood under a clear sky. Classic Stone Town architecture — this is likely the Treasures of Zanzibar House or a nearby courtyard typical of the historic district.\"},{\"heading\":\"Swimming & Beach Notes\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md: For Zanzibar swimming, the north coast (Nungwi area) offers more consistent conditions vs. east/south coasts where low tide limits access. Kiwengwa is on the east coast, so tide-dependent swimming should be expected. The markdown recommends north-coast beaches for better water access.\"},{\"heading\":\"Zanzibar Mandatory Insurance\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: Zanzibar requires separate mandatory travel insurance from the Zanzibar Insurance Corporation (ZIC). Cost is $44 per traveler, $88 total for both — listed in the costs sheet.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"Zanzibar is a 6-night split stay combining cultural Stone Town and beach relaxation in Kiwengwa, anchored by a confirmed dinner at The Rock on Aug 15. The local driving permit (~$15) and Zanzibar insurance ($88) are mandatory add-ons. Swimming is tide-dependent on the east coast. The photo captures the classic Stone Town aesthetic: whitewashed, arched, and wooden-balconied.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n{\"seq\":221,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n{\"seq\":222,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":223,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":224,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":225,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"// I'm being asked to build a specialist space for \\\"Cairo Stopovers\\\" using the research that's already provided. // The item contains the research findings directly. I delegate to the architect with this fully-formed scope. const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n{\"seq\":226,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_18_d6914e2a\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Cairo Stopovers.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Cairo Stopovers\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of both Cairo stopovers: hotels, sightseeing plans, flights, and costs?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Cairo Stopovers\",\"executive_summary\":\"Cairo features twice in the itinerary as arrival and departure stopovers, anchoring the whole trip. Stopover 1 (Aug 3–5) includes the Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza. Stopover 2 (Aug 19–20) covers Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, and Coptic Cairo. Both legs are fully booked with distinct hotels.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Stopover 1 — Arrival (Aug 3–5)\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Hotel: Eileen Hotel, Cairo — Aug 3–5, 2 nights, $102 total. Address: 21 Youssef El-Gendy St, Abdeen, Downtown Cairo (near Tahrir Square). Phone: +20 15 56434043, email: info@eileenhotel.com. Flight in: ATH→CAI, Aegean A3932, Aug 3, 06:55–08:50, ref ZZJQUU. Flight out: CAI→DAR, EgyptAir, Aug 4, 22:40–04:20+1. Sightseeing plan: Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza. Note: late checkout Aug 5 is noted but not used for sleep since flight departs late on Aug 4.\"},{\"heading\":\"Stopover 2 — Departure (Aug 19–20)\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Hotel: Ramses Hilton, Cairo — Aug 19–20, 1 night, $87 total. Flight in: DAR→CAI, EgyptAir, Aug 19, 05:20–11:05. Flight out: CAI→ATH, Aegean A3935, Aug 20, 19:55–22:00, ref ZZL22S. Sightseeing plan: Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, Coptic Cairo. Taxi needed between Citadel and Coptic Cairo.\"},{\"heading\":\"Egypt E-Visa Requirement\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and costs sheet: Egypt e-visa is multiple-entry, $65 per person, $130 total for both travelers. Each traveler applies separately. A printed copy is mandatory.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"Cairo bookends the trip with two distinct 2-day/1-night stays. The first is museum-and-pyramids focused from a downtown base; the second is a whirlwind historical Cairo tour from the Ramses Hilton. Both require the same multiple-entry e-visa ($130 total, printed copy required). Combined lodging cost is $189.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n{\"seq\":227,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n{\"seq\":228,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":229,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":230,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":231,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"// Build Safari Logistics specialist from the inventoried scope. // We have all the source material in the item already — no external research needed. // Delegate directly to the architect with the pre-researched item. const result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\"}\n{\"seq\":232,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"fork:build_specialist\",\"nodeId\":\"fork_16_9f9d0a63\",\"text\":\"delegate\",\"args\":[\"system-architect\",\"architect\",\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"query\":\"Build a specialist space for Safari Logistics.\",\"context\":{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of the 3-day Suricata Safaris camping safari: contacts (Richard), payment schedule, vehicle requirements, itinerary, and the Arusha lodging that frames the safari?\",\"research\":{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"executive_summary\":\"The safari is a 3-day group camping safari (Aug 7–9) operated by Suricata Safaris Ltd, contact Richard. It covers Tarangire NP, Lake Manyara NP, and Ngorongoro Crater, with overnight at Twiga Camp Site and Jevas Hotel. Total cost is $1,200 with a $240 deposit paid and $960 balance due on arrival. Arusha serves as the logistical base with pre- and post-safari hotel stays.\",\"findings\":[{\"heading\":\"Operator & Contact\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Suricata Safaris Ltd — Richard, phone: +255 763 222 293, email: info@suricatasafaris.com. The driver/guide at Ngorongoro was Emmanuel (not Richard), indicating Suricata uses multiple driver-guides. Richard appears to be the office/logistics contact.\"},{\"heading\":\"Itinerary & Accommodations\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 7–9, 3-day group camping safari. Day 1: Tarangire National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB — full board). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater → overnight Jevas Hotel (HB — half board). Park fees are separate from the safari package: Tarangire entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Lake Manyara entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Ngorongoro fees $578.20 total (entry $141.60 + crater service $141.60 + vehicle descent $295). These park fees total $814.20 and are listed separately in the costs sheet, meaning the $1,200 safari package likely covers guide, vehicle, camping gear, and meals but excludes park fees — or the breakdown in costs splits them for tracking.\"},{\"heading\":\"Payment Schedule\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Total safari cost: $1,200. Deposit paid (20%): $240. Balance due: $960. Payment method: cash on arrival (USD, post-2009 notes only) OR online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Cash is preferred to avoid the 5% surcharge ($48 extra).\"},{\"heading\":\"Vehicle Information\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and NCAA tariffs: Suricata Safaris provides a 4×4 safari vehicle (required for Ngorongoro Crater descent — only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight allowed on crater floor). The vehicle must be a registered company vehicle with a valid TALA license per Tourism Act No. 29, 2008. The NCAA vehicle descent fee is $295 per trip (non-EA registered).\"},{\"heading\":\"Arusha Base (Pre- and Post-Safari)\",\"detail\":\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Aug 5–7: Serengeti Villa, Arusha, 2 nights, $62 total. Phone: +255 757 757 928. Aug 9–11: Kutoka Lodge, Arusha, 2 nights, $96 total. These frame the safari and serve as staging/rest points. Flight ARK arrival Aug 5 at 12:00 (Precision Air TC144); departure ARK→ZNZ Aug 11 at 12:40 (Precision Air TC145).\"},{\"heading\":\"Park Fees Summary (Excluded from Safari Package?)\",\"detail\":\"From trip-costs.xlsx costs sheet, park fees are listed as separate line items totaling $814.20: Tarangire $118 + Lake Manyara $118 + Ngorongoro entry $141.60 + Ngorongoro crater service $141.60 + Ngorongoro vehicle descent $295. The safari package ($1,200) may or may not include these — the costs sheet lists them independently but doesn't clarify whether Richard's package covers them. This is worth confirming with Richard alongside the ranger tip question.\"}],\"conclusion\":\"The 3-day Suricata Safaris package is the operational backbone of the Tanzania leg, with Richard as the key contact. The $960 balance (cash, post-2009 USD) is the largest outstanding payment. Two open questions for Richard: (1) is the ranger tip legitimate/expected? (2) are the listed park fees included in the $1,200 package or additional? Arusha provides comfortable bookend stays at Serengeti Villa and Kutoka Lodge.\",\"sources\":[]}}}]}\n{\"seq\":233,\"type\":\"node_start\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"delegate\"}\n{\"seq\":234,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":235,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — run the synthesis\"}\n{\"seq\":236,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":237,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_22_c041adc7\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":238,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 —\"}\n{\"seq\":239,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":240,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_21_ad6eb564\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":241,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"// Turn\"}\n{\"seq\":242,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":243,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":244,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — run the build\"}\n{\"seq\":245,\"type\":\"turn_end\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":246,\"type\":\"llm_request\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_23_3e6e4d70\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":247,\"type\":\"statement\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":248,\"type\":\"llm_progress\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"\"}\n{\"seq\":249,\"type\":\"llm_response\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"// Turn 1 — seed the build pipeline with the research already handed to us in context. // No deep-research; synthesize_and_run builds (design → write → validate → register) inside the tasklist. const t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', { topic: context.topic, goal: context.goal, research: JSON.stringify(context.research), });\"}\n{\"seq\":250,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"tasklist\",\"args\":[\"synthesize_and_run\",{\"topic\":\"Safari Logistics\",\"goal\":\"What are the details of the 3-day Suricata Safaris camping safari: contacts (Richard), payment schedule, vehicle requirements, itinerary, and the Arusha lodging that frames the safari?\",\"research\":\"{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Safari Logistics\\\",\\\"executive_summary\\\":\\\"The safari is a 3-day group camping safari (Aug 7–9) operated by Suricata Safaris Ltd, contact Richard. It covers Tarangire NP, Lake Manyara NP, and Ngorongoro Crater, with overnight at Twiga Camp Site and Jevas Hotel. Total cost is $1,200 with a $240 deposit paid and $960 balance due on arrival. Arusha serves as the logistical base with pre- and post-safari hotel stays.\\\",\\\"findings\\\":[{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Operator & Contact\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md: Suricata Safaris Ltd — Richard, phone: +255 763 222 293, email: info@suricatasafaris.com. The driver/guide at Ngorongoro was Emmanuel (not Richard), indicating Suricata uses multiple driver-guides. Richard appears to be the office/logistics contact.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Itinerary & Accommodations\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx legs sheet: Aug 7–9, 3-day group camping safari. Day 1: Tarangire National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB — full board). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park → overnight Twiga Camp Site (FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater → overnight Jevas Hotel (HB — half board). Park fees are separate from the safari package: Tarangire entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Lake Manyara entrance $118 (2 pax × $59 peak season), Ngorongoro fees $578.20 total (entry $141.60 + crater service $141.60 + vehicle descent $295). These park fees total $814.20 and are listed separately in the costs sheet, meaning the $1,200 safari package likely covers guide, vehicle, camping gear, and meals but excludes park fees — or the breakdown in costs splits them for tracking.\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Payment Schedule\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Total safari cost: $1,200. Deposit paid (20%): $240. Balance due: $960. Payment method: cash on arrival (USD, post-2009 notes only) OR online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Cash is preferred to avoid the 5% surcharge ($48 extra).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Vehicle Information\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and NCAA tariffs: Suricata Safaris provides a 4×4 safari vehicle (required for Ngorongoro Crater descent — only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight allowed on crater floor). The vehicle must be a registered company vehicle with a valid TALA license per Tourism Act No. 29, 2008. The NCAA vehicle descent fee is $295 per trip (non-EA registered).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Arusha Base (Pre- and Post-Safari)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From tanzaniamemories.md and trip-costs.xlsx: Aug 5–7: Serengeti Villa, Arusha, 2 nights, $62 total. Phone: +255 757 757 928. Aug 9–11: Kutoka Lodge, Arusha, 2 nights, $96 total. These frame the safari and serve as staging/rest points. Flight ARK arrival Aug 5 at 12:00 (Precision Air TC144); departure ARK→ZNZ Aug 11 at 12:40 (Precision Air TC145).\\\"},{\\\"heading\\\":\\\"Park Fees Summary (Excluded from Safari Package?)\\\",\\\"detail\\\":\\\"From trip-costs.xlsx costs sheet, park fees are listed as separate line items totaling $814.20: Tarangire $118 + Lake Manyara $118 + Ngorongoro entry $141.60 + Ngorongoro crater service $141.60 + Ngorongoro vehicle descent $295. The safari package ($1,200) may or may not include these — the costs sheet lists them independently but doesn't clarify whether Richard's package covers them. This is worth confirming with Richard alongside the ranger tip question.\\\"}],\\\"conclusion\\\":\\\"The 3-day Suricata Safaris package is the operational backbone of the Tanzania leg, with Richard as the key contact. The $960 balance (cash, post-2009 USD) is the largest outstanding payment. Two open questions for Richard: (1) is the ranger tip legitimate/expected? (2) are the listed park fees included in the $1,200 package or additional? Arusha provides comfortable bookend stays at Serengeti Villa and Kutoka Lodge.\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[]}\"}]}\n{\"seq\":251,\"type\":\"yield_resolved\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_24_ccd3f485\",\"text\":\"tasklist\"}\n{\"seq\":252,\"type\":\"variables\",\"context