{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_Sl1Sw5RyW4raiyLXDRpqDZtC","type":"tool_result","content":"45\t   * Observed live (10-family-recipes): the builder seeded a row from material the user handed over\n46\t   * and captured every operational detail of it perfectly — while dropping WHO the material was\n47\t   * credited to. It even chose a `source` column, then filled it with the CHANNEL the material\n48\t   * arrived on rather than the name the material itself states. The user had asked, in as many\n49\t   * words, not to lose any of it.\n50\t   *\n51\t   * The operational content is the half a person can always look up again; the attribution is the\n52\t   * half they cannot reconstruct from anywhere else — and is very often why the material was kept.\n53\t   * The existing rule covers figures and contacts the source STATES; it did not cover the name it\n54\t   * is credited to, nor the near-miss of recording the envelope instead of the fact.\n55\t   */\n56\t  it('tells the builder to keep the attribution the material carries — and not to record the transport instead', () => {\n57\t    const instruct = readFileSync(join(SYSTEM_SPACES, 'system-appbuilder', 'agents', 'automator', 'instruct.md'), 'utf8');\n58\t\n59\t    expect(\n60\t      instruct,\n61\t      'the automator must be told to keep WHO/WHERE material came from on the record, not just its operational content',\n62\t    ).toMatch(/attribution|credited_to|provenance/i);\n63\t\n64\t    // The near-miss guard: a `source` field filled with \"from an attachment\" LOOKS done and is not.\n65\t    expect(\n66\t      instruct,\n67\t      'the automator must be warned that recording the CHANNEL the material arrived on is not the attribution',\n68\t    ).toMatch(/transport is not the attribution|channel the material arrived on/i);\n69\t  });\n70\t});\n71\t\n72\tdescribe('system-architect/architect — custom choice components', () => {\n73\t  it('tells the space builder to handle a dism