{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_cx06rniYmw6IiT5CydeHQ4wc","type":"tool_result","content":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md:46:The child VM is built by the shared `createChildVM` (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/fork/fork.ts:283-305`) with a **fork** capability profile (`forkCapabilities`, `sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/capability.ts:94-97`): headless (no `ask`), non-orchestrating (no `fork`/`tasklist`), `delegate` only when the task opts in, and write/`registerSpace` gated by the role. A stray `ask()`/`fork()`/`tasklist()` call fails **typecheck** (a clean retryable error) because those declarations are absent from the fork's ambient DTS — not injected, not declared (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/fork/fork.ts:326-343`, `sdk/org/libs/core/src/typecheck/library-dts.ts:3-13`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md:60:Read-only is enforced physically: `roleProfile(role).allowWrite` is false for explore/plan (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/fork/roles.ts#roleProfile`), which blocks the internal `writeFileRaw` host write and rejects mutating shell commands at injection (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/globals/host-tools.ts:223-228`, `:186-187`). Those raw primitives are internal-only — never on any agent's model DTS regardless of role — so there is no model declaration to drop; a fork's generic scratch fs/shell is instead gated on `fs:scratch` (above). Read-only roles also lose `registerSpace` and get the `allowWrite`-intersected subset of app capabilities — every mutating grant (`db:write`/`pages:write`/…) is dropped, and because `intersectAppCaps` does not keep `fs:scratch` a read-only fork drops scratch too (`scratchFs:false`) (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/capability.ts#intersectAppCaps`, `:101-105`). Per-role model assignment (`roleModels`) lets cheap explore/plan forks run on a cheaper model (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/fork/roles.ts:60-71`).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md:109:  - `preloadSpaceDirs` — the scanned dirs (`session-manager.ts:1114-1130`), which `Session.start`/rehydrate loads into `dynamicSpaces` up front so they are **delegatable immediately** (`session.ts:236-245`, `427-433`; one bad dir logs a warn and is isolated, it does not abort startup).\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md:114:## Runtime registration — `registerSpace`\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md:116:`registerSpace(dir)` is a value-yielding global (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/globals/register-space.ts#createRegisterSpaceGlobal`) that loads a space at `dir` into the live registry so `delegate()` can reach it *this session*. It returns `{ ok, spaceKey, agentSlug, error? }` where `spaceKey === dir` (the key to pass to `delegate()`) and `agentSlug` is the first agent found.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md:118:Resolution has two sites, both writing the **same shared `dynamicSpaces` Map**:\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md:119:- **Top-level session** (`session.ts:816-826`): `loadSpace(dir)` → `this.dynamicSpaces.set(dir, space)`; on failure returns `{ ok:false, error }` rather than throwing.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/spaces-loading.md:122:`Session.dynamicSpaces` is a shared mutable `Map` (`session.ts:109-113`). When building a delegate's `spaceMap` (`session.ts:925-939`), the session seeds it with its own space + `dependentSpaces`, adds every system space (always delegatable), then merges in every `dynamicSpaces` entry.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:38:| `registerSpace(dir)` | value-yield (`kind:'registerSpace'`) | `CapabilityProfile.registerSpace` | session; write-capable forks; **never** delegates `sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/bootstrap.ts:234` |\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:172:## `registerSpace(dir)`\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:175:run. Value yield (`kind:'registerSpace'`), resolving to\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:178:loads the space and stores it in the shared `dynamicSpaces` map\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:182:const reg = await registerSpace('/tmp/architect-spaces/analyst');\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:188:**Gate:** `registerSpace: true` for sessions; for a fork it follows the role's write\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:189:capability (`registerSpace: allowWrite` — read-only `explore`/`plan` roles lose it); a\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime-globals/session-and-utils.md:372:- **`registerSpace` DTS is unconditional.** It is declared in `COMMON_DTS`\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/delegation.md:60:**2. Yield-time (runtime gate).** Every delegate path calls the *same* `isDelegateAllowed(policy, packageName, agentName, dynamicSpaces)` and, on refusal, throws `formatDelegateDenial(...)`:\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/delegation.md:63:export function isDelegateAllowed(policy, packageName, agentName, dynamicSpaces?) {\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/delegation.md:68:  if (policy.allowRegistered && matchesRegisteredSpace(packageName, dynamicSpaces)) {\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/delegation.md:86:Matching tolerates the ref grammar (`self` / `space/agent` / `npm:pkg/agent`, each with an optional `#action`; parsed by `parseDelegateRef`, `sdk/org/libs/core/src/delegate/ref.ts`) plus symmetric directory-suffix tolerance — `fuzzyNameMatch` treats `\"a/b/c\"` and `\"c\"` as a match in either direction (`sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/target-match.ts:23-26`, `refMatchesDelegateCall` `:34-51`). `registered:*` is satisfied when the package name matches a key/dir/packageName in the s