{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_8xCA8enRRlGpD6juTJrpQlg8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: finalize\n3\toutput:\n4\t  spaceKey: string\n5\t  agentSlug: string\n6\t  actionId: string\n7\t  query: string\n8\t  ok: boolean\n9\t  errors: string\n10\tdependsOn: [design, register, validate]\n11\tgoal: true\n12\trole: explore\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tPackage the result for the caller. This is the GOAL task — it ALWAYS runs and ALWAYS resolves a\n16\tuniform result (success OR a structured failure), so the caller can decide whether to run the\n17\tnew agent. The original user request `topic` is in scope as a seed variable. Emit:\n18\t\n19\tconst ok = register.ok === true && register.spaceKey !== \"\";\n20\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n21\t  spaceKey: register.spaceKey,\n22\t  agentSlug: register.agentSlug,\n23\t  actionId: design.actionId,\n24\t  query: topic,\n25\t  ok,\n26\t  errors: ok ? \"\" : (validate.ok ? (register.error || \"registration failed\") : validate.errors),\n27\t});\n28\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_VsdMSqwzult8golfb0xW5BYw","session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"651d08fe-d8dd-44b3-ab9e-1dda3baf670b","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:00:12.660Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace parallel specialist persistence"}
