{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_uIKUSYN7Pd5BLlPU2VBa7v9X","type":"tool_result","content":"sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/bracelet-purchase.md:3:Two beaded bracelets bought from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for Athina Mari. Cost: approximately $20–25 USD or ~35,000 TZS.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/ranger-tip.md:3:A ~5,000 TZS cash tip was expected at the gate for the ranger, separate from all park fees. Nobody told the travelers about this beforehand. Action needed: ask Richard about the ranger tip before settling the safari balance payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/index.md:8:Driver: The safari driver on crater day was Emmanuel — not Richard who handles bookings from the Suricata office.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/index.md:10:Bracelet Purchase: Two beaded bracelets bought from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for Athina Mari. Cost: approximately $20–25 USD or ~35,000 TZS.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/index.md:12:Ranger Tip: A ~5,000 TZS cash tip was expected at the gate for the ranger, separate from all park fees. Nobody told the travelers about this beforehand. Action needed: ask Richard about the ranger tip before settling the safari balance payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/driver.md:3:The safari driver on crater day was Emmanuel — not Richard who handles bookings from the Suricata office.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/ranger-tip-surprise.md:3:An unexpected cash tip of approximately **5,000 TZS** was expected at the gate for the ranger, separate from all park fees. **Nobody mentioned this beforehand.** The travelers were caught off-guard by this additional out-of-pocket expense.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/driver-identity.md:3:On the Ngorongoro Crater day, the safari driver was **Emmanuel** — not Richard, who handles bookings from the Suricata office. This distinction matters because Richard is the primary contact for reservations and the safari balance, while Emmanuel was the on-the-ground driver for the crater excursion itself.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-regs/knowledge/ngorongoro/contacts/emergency-and-regional.md:8:- +255 27 253 7046\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/agents/ngorongoro-voice-memories/instruct.md:12:    description: \"Recall personal memories and practical trip notes from the Ngorongoro Crater voice memo: driver Emmanuel, two beaded bracelets for Athina Mari (~$20–25 USD), and the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip needing clarification with Richard.\"\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/bracelet-purchase.md:3:Two beaded bracelets were purchased from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for **Athina Mari**. The estimated cost was approximately **$20–25 USD** or roughly **35,000 TZS**. This was an informal, personal transaction at the rim — a small souvenir moment captured in the voice memo alongside the day's main wildlife viewing.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/cairo-stopover-advisor/knowledge/cairo/logistics/flights.md:5:- **ATH→CAI**: Aegean A3932, Aug 3, 06:55–08:50, ref ZZJQUU (arrival stopover)\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/index.md:8:**Driver identity**: The safari driver on crater day was Emmanuel — not Richard who handles bookings from the Suricata office.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/index.md:10:**Bracelet purchase**: Two beaded bracelets bought from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for Athina Mari. Cost: approximately $20–25 USD or ~35,000 TZS.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/index.md:12:**Ranger tip surprise**: A ~5,000 TZS cash tip was expected at the gate for the ranger, separate from all park fees. Nobody told the travelers about this beforehand. Action needed: ask Richard about the ranger tip before settling the safari balance payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-voice-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-crater/index.md:14:These details add personal texture — the bracelets, Emmanuel as driver — and one actionable financial loose end (the ranger tip) to surface alongside formal itinerary and costs.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/arusha-safari-planner/knowledge/tanzania/safari-itinerary/ngorongoro-crater.md:3:The Ngorongoro Crater is Day 3 (Aug 9) and the grand finale of the safari. This UNESCO World Heritage Site is the world's largest intact volcanic caldera, home to an estimated 25,000 large animals including the Big Five (lion, leopard, elephant, buffalo, and the rare black rhino). The day begins with a descent into the crater floor for a half-day game drive, followed by lunch. Accommodation shifts to Jevas Hotel on a half-board basis. Ngorongoro fees are more complex: the entry permit is $70.80 per person, the crater service fee is another $70.80 per person, and there is a vehicle descent fee of $295.00 (per vehicle/trip, non-East African). Nights at Ngorongoro are cold — warm layers are essential.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-regs/knowledge/ngorongoro/contacts/official-contacts.md:13:Hotline: +255 27 253 7046  \nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/cairo-stopover-advisor/knowledge/cairo/sightseeing/grand-egyptian-museum.md:3:The Grand Egyptian Museum (GEM) is the newest and largest archaeological museum in the world, located on the Giza Plateau roughly 2 km from the Pyramids. It houses over 100,000 artifacts, including the complete Tutankhamun collection displayed together for the first time. The museum opened in phases starting in late 2024 and is designed to handle up to 15,000 visitors daily. Key galleries include the Grand Hall with a colossal statue of Ramesses II, the staircase gallery with 60+ monumental pieces, and the immersive Tutankhamun galleries. For the arrival stopover (Aug 3–5), the GEM is the morning sightseeing priority before heading to the Pyramids. Travelers staying at the Eileen Hotel near Tahrir Square can reach the museum in approximately 45–60 minutes by taxi or ride-hailing app (Uber/Careem). Recommended visit duration: 3–4 hours. Tickets can be purchased online in advance; standard adult entry is approximately EGP 1,000–1,200 for non-Egyptians. Photography is permitted in most galleries (no flash). On-site amenities include a café, gift shop, and restaurant with Pyramid views.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/suricata-safari-finances/knowledge/tanzania-safari/suricata-booking/ranger-tip-question.md:3:A voice memo reveals that a ~5,000 TZS cash ranger tip is expected at the Ngorongoro gate, separate from park fees. The travelers were not informed about this beforehand. Vasilis needs to ask Richard about this ranger tip before settling the $960 safari balance, to avoid being caught without sufficient cash at the gate.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/suricata-safari-finances/knowledge/tanzania-safari/suricata-booking/index.md:6:Suricata Safaris Ltd 3-day group camping safari booking status. Covers the total package cost and deposit-paid vs. balance-due breakdown (package-cost-payment), Richard's contact details for clarifying outstanding questions (operator-contact), and the unresolved ~5,000 TZS ranger tip expected at the Ngorongoro gate that must be clarified with the operator before settling the balance (ranger-tip-question).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"c23d9867-7c05-41e3-96a1-4673e939d238","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:14:01.296Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/bracelet-purchase.md:3:Two beaded bracelets bought from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for Athina Mari. Cost: approximately $20–25 USD or ~35,000 TZS.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-crater-memories/knowledge/safari/ngorongoro-day/ranger-tip.md:3:A ~5,000 TZS cash tip was expected at the gate for the ranger, separate from all park fees. Nobody told the travelers about this beforehand. Action needed: ask Richard about the ranger tip before settling the safari balance payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro