{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_26ef2554-75a5-4508-9184-be809c611709","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_dTfJYS1x1W4l8Ye1nbKp35wR","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/01-inventory.md","old_string":"Identify every independently owned scope in the supplied material. `request`, `sourceSummary`,\n`attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every supplied document with\n`readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope has its own facts and\ndeserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because it has few facts. A\nscope is a stable part of the user's material (such as a location, stage, person, client, or piece of\nequipment), NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, or fact. Include every stable scope\nrepresented in the source, not only the most detailed ones.\n\nFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\nwith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\nin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\nis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:","new_string":"Identify every independently owned scope in the supplied material. `request`, `sourceSummary`,\n`attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every supplied document with\n`readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope has its own facts and\ndeserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because it has few facts. A\nscope is a stable part of the user's material (such as a location, stage, person, client, or piece of\nequipment), NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, fact, photo, memory, shared overview, or\ncross-cutting finance grouping. Combine subparts only when they are one uninterrupted operational\nstage; otherwise give each independently owned location or stage its own scope. Include every stable\nscope represented in the source, not only the most detailed ones.\n\nFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\nwith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\nin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\nis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:"}}],"model":"gpt-5.6-terra","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7fe4138-ba72-469d-8c93-8d7c68dc56e8","uuid":"ad8bf54f-1277-40a5-939c-07489e62faf8"}
